<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5082/105.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Special Commissioner <persName type="from">Buchanan</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Willemstadt</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-10"><hi rend="italic">February 10,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Buchanan says the form of submission of the Orinoco case, which was
                            made contingent on settlement of Bermudez case, having been agreed upon,
                            favorable and final action on both took place to-day.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>